<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.WindowSystemInfoSDL3" Title="WindowSystemInfoSDL3 class" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.PlatformBindings">PlatformBindings</PageRef> ->
    WindowSystemInfoSDL3
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Declaration">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[class WindowSystemInfoSDL3;]]></Code>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>WindowSystemInfoSDL3</TypeRef> class is an SDL3 helper that detects SDL's active video driver and builds the matching platform-specific <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IRenderer.WindowSystemInfoBase">IRenderer.WindowSystemInfoBase</PageRef> derived structure for renderer initialization.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
      Availability: Builds where <TypeRef>COBALT_RENDERER_SDL3_SUPPORT</TypeRef> is enabled.
    </Paragraph>
    <Note Type="Important">
      <Paragraph>
        On Linux with both Xlib and XCB support compiled in, the SDL helper selects Xlib for the SDL <TypeRef>x11</TypeRef> video driver because the Xlib branch is tested first.
      </Paragraph>
    </Note>
  </Section>
